wikipedia_page.main: The Rt Hon. William Wentworth FitzWilliam Dick (28 October 1805 – 15 September 1892), known as William Wentworth FitzWilliam Hume until 1864, was an Irish Conservative politician.He was elected as one of the two Members of Parliament (MPs) for Wicklow in 1852 and held the seat until 1880, when he was defeated.
